             <lg> 
              <l>There were three in the meadow by the brook</l>
          <l>Gathering up windrows, piling cocks of hay,</l> 
          <l>With an eye always lifted toward the west</l>
          <l>Where an irregular sun-boardered cloud</l>
          <l>Darkly advanced with a perpetual dagger</l>
          <l>Flickering across its bosom. Suddenly</l>
          <l>One helper, thrusting pitchfork in the ground,</l>
          <l>Marched himself off the field and home. One stayed.</l>
          <l>The town-bred farmer failed to understand.</l>
          <l>"What is there wrong?"</l>
          <l>"Something you just now said."</l>
          <l>"What did I say?"</l>
          <l>"About our taking pains."</l>
          <l>To cock the hay?--because it's going to shower?<l>
          <l>I said that more than half an hour ago. <l>
          <l>I said it to myself as much as you.<l>
